    <!-- Responsive: stack columns on mobile -->
    <style>
      @media (max-width: 640px) {
        section div[style*="grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr"] {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
          gap: 32px !important;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT PAYNE COUNTY DETENTION CENTER — unique local content -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: var(--slate-50);">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">About Payne County Detention Center</h2>
      <div style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">The Payne County Detention Center is the main county jail for Payne County, located at 606 S Husband St in Stillwater, Oklahoma 74074. Operated by the Payne County Sheriff's Office, this facility is the primary detention center for the county, handling long-term holds, pre-trial detention, and inmates serving sentences under one year. The detention center is separate from the Stillwater City Jail, which is a short-term municipal holding facility. Inmates arrested by Stillwater Police are often transferred to the Payne County Detention Center within 72 hours of their initial booking.</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">The detention center is located in downtown Stillwater, just south of the Payne County Courthouse on Husband Street. The Payne County Court Clerk's office is located upstairs in Suite 207 of the same building complex, where cash bail can be paid during business hours (Monday through Friday, 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM). After business hours and on weekends, exact cash bail can be paid directly at the detention center, but using a bail bondsman is often the fastest and most convenient option.</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 14px;">Because Angel Bail Bonds is based right here in Stillwater, we can respond to Payne County Detention Center faster than any other facility we serve. We are just minutes away and have an established working relationship with the detention center staff. We understand their booking procedures, their processing timeline, and we know exactly what paperwork is needed to expedite a release. Typical release times at this facility range from 1-2 hours after the bond is posted, which is among the fastest of any county facility in the region.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Inmate Lookup and Communication</h3>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;">You can look up inmates currently held at the Payne County Detention Center by searching the online inmate roster at paynecountyok.gov/inmate-search, which is updated approximately every hour. You can also call the detention center directly at (405) 372-4522 for inmate information. For visitation, in-person visits are available on Wednesdays with 15-minute sessions at the Sheriff's Office lobby kiosk at no charge. Remote video visitation is available daily through CityTeleCoin -- register at CityTeleCoin.com to schedule a video visit. Inmates can also receive mail and have funds deposited into their commissary accounts.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ — compact accordion -->
  <section style="padding: 40px 1.5rem; background: white;">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px;">
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">How do I bail someone out of Payne County Detention Center?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Call Angel Bail Bonds at (405) 614-3000. We need the inmate's full name, booking number, and charges. We handle the paperwork and post the bond directly at the detention center. Most releases take 1-2 hours after the bond is posted.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">Where do I pay bail for Payne County Detention Center inmates?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Cash bail can be paid at the Payne County Court Clerk's office (Suite 207, 606 S Husband St, Stillwater) Monday-Friday 8am-5pm. After hours, exact cash is accepted at the detention center itself. Or call Angel Bail Bonds and we handle everything for you 24/7.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">What are visitation hours at Payne County Detention Center?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">In-person visitation is available on Wednesdays with 15-minute visits at the Sheriff's Office lobby kiosk (free). Remote video visitation through CityTeleCoin is available daily. Register at CityTeleCoin.com to schedule visits.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">How much does a bail bond cost?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Angel Bail Bonds offers competitive rates on bail bonds. Contact us at (405) 614-3000 to discuss pricing for your situation. We work with you so finances don't delay your loved one's release.</p>
        </details>
        <details style="background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 18px; cursor: pointer; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100);">
          <summary style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--slate-800);">How do I look up an inmate at Payne County Detention Center?</summary>
          <p style="color: var(--slate-500); margin-top: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Search the online inmate roster at paynecountyok.gov/inmate-search (updated hourly) or call the detention center at (405) 372-4522. You'll need the inmate's name to look up their booking info, charges, and bail amount.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Pages -->
  <section style="padding: 24px 1.5rem 0; background: var(--slate-50);">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <p style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--slate-400); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px;">Also Serving</p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/payne-county-jail-bail-bonds" style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--blue); text-decoration: none; padding: 6px 14px; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100); border-radius: 6px;">Payne County Jail →</a>
        <a href="/stillwater-city-jail-bail-bonds" style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--blue); text-decoration: none; padding: 6px 14px; background: white; border: 1px solid var(--slate-100); border-radius: 6px;">Stillwater City Jail →</a>
